Motoring website Cars.co.za has announced the finalists of its 2020/21 consumer awards. The 39 finalists for the 2020/21 programme were selected by the extended Cars.co.za editorial team – each member scored the 65 pre-selected semi-finalists individually across 13 respective categories. Once the scores were tallied, three finalists were identified in each of the segments. “We made some revisions to the categories to make sure that they are in line with what South Africans are shopping for in the new vehicle market, but also factored in which segments had seen significant activity in terms of new launches,” said Cars.co.za consumer experience manager Hannes Oosthuizen. “We also consider pricing movements, to make sure that our categories remain relevant to the consumer,” he said. Entry-level Hyundai Atos 1.1 Motion
